WEBVTT

1
00:03:14.060 --> 00:03:15.510
Are you crazy?

2
00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:17.320
You'll wake up
the whole neighborhood.

3
00:03:17.350 --> 00:03:19.180
- Hi. Mom.
- Don't "Hi. Mom" me.

4
00:03:19.210 --> 00:03:20.670
What are you still doing up?
It's past 1:00.

5
00:03:20.710 --> 00:03:24.510
- I thought I'd wait for you.
- Well. I'm home.

6
00:03:24.550 --> 00:03:26.410
Now you can get to sleep.
Come on.

7
00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:27.550
Andale.

8
00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:30.980
I'm really not tired.

9
00:03:31.010 --> 00:03:33.670
Kristen. don't start with me.
You know what your shrink said.

10
00:03:33.710 --> 00:03:35.260
He's full of it.

11
00:03:35.310 --> 00:03:36.900
I'm not going to let you
get me into an argument.

12
00:03:36.940 --> 00:03:38.440
Now get to sleep.

13
00:03:38.470 --> 00:03:43.560
Mom. I'm still having
those awful dreams.

14
00:03:43.600 --> 00:03:45.760
Elaine.
where do you keep the bourbon?

15
00:03:46.760 --> 00:03:49.930
I'll be right down.
I've got a guest.

16
00:03:49.960 --> 00:03:51.970
And you don't want
to keep him waiting?

17
00:03:52.010 --> 00:03:53.760
That's right. I don't.

18
00:03:56.270 --> 00:03:57.380
Good night.

19
00:04:45.770 --> 00:04:50.080
One. two.
Freddy's coming for you

20
00:04:50.130 --> 00:04:54.410
Three. four.
better lock your door

21
00:04:54.440 --> 00:04:58.890
Five. six. grab a crucifix

22
00:04:58.920 --> 00:05:03.590
Seven. eight. gonna stay up late

23
00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:08.100
Nine. ten. never sleep again

24
00:05:08.140 --> 00:05:12.400
One. two.
Freddy's coming for you

25
00:05:12.430 --> 00:05:15.980
Three. four.
better lock your door

26
00:05:16.010 --> 00:05:19.950
Five. six. grab a crucifix

27
00:05:19.990 --> 00:05:24.680
Seven. eight. gonna stay up late

28
00:05:24.720 --> 00:05:26.890
Nine. ten...

29
00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:40.840
Hi. What's your name?

30
00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:43.820
Kristen. What's yours?

31
00:05:46.320 --> 00:05:48.230
What is this place?

32
00:05:50.390 --> 00:05:52.810
I got to go now.

33
00:05:53.910 --> 00:05:55.570
Wait. little girl.
Don't go in there!

34
00:05:57.390 --> 00:05:59.430
Little girl?

35
00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:42.830
This is where he takes us.

36
00:06:43.830 --> 00:06:44.780
Come on. We're going.

37
00:06:55.670 --> 00:06:57.320
Freddy's home.

38
00:07:56.920 --> 00:07:59.190
Put me down. You're hurting me.

39
00:09:11.870 --> 00:09:14.550
And in local news. two more
teenage deaths have occurred...

40
00:09:14.590 --> 00:09:15.770
both suicides.

41
00:09:15.810 --> 00:09:17.750
County health officials
are at a loss to explain...

42
00:09:17.790 --> 00:09:19.770
this alarming trend.

43
00:09:19.810 --> 00:09:23.390
Nothing like a little
cheery news to start the day.

44
00:09:23.420 --> 00:09:27.220
Doc. I got a new theory
about all these suicides.

45
00:09:27.260 --> 00:09:30.110
Don't hold back on us. Max.
We need all the help we can get.

46
00:09:30.150 --> 00:09:32.450
It's fucked-up chromosomes.
Think about it.

47
00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:34.930
All their parents dropped acid
during the sixties.

48
00:09:34.970 --> 00:09:36.380
It beats Simms' theory.

49
00:09:36.420 --> 00:09:38.930
She thinks it's sex.
drugs. and rock 'n' roll.

50
00:09:38.970 --> 00:09:41.460
Shit.
That's what keeps people alive.

51
00:09:42.430 --> 00:09:44.280
Hi. Taryn.

52
00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:46.900
You don't look so hot. kid.
Are you getting some sleep?

53
00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:49.630
I didn't think so.

54
00:09:49.670 --> 00:09:50.750
Good morning. Dr. Gordon.

55
00:09:50.790 --> 00:09:52.570
Good morning. Jennifer.
How are the burns?

56
00:09:52.610 --> 00:09:54.170
Regular. menthol. ultra-light.

57
00:09:54.210 --> 00:09:55.610
They're healing up nicely.

58
00:09:55.650 --> 00:09:59.450
I've been good. When do I get
my cigarette privileges back?

59
00:09:59.490 --> 00:10:01.460
Don't hold your breath.

60
00:10:02.180 --> 00:10:04.250
- Phillip.
- Hey. Doc.

61
00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:14.810
How is he?

62
00:10:14.850 --> 00:10:16.280
He's cooling down.

63
00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:18.180
If he continues having
these outbursts...

64
00:10:18.210 --> 00:10:20.390
I'll have to have him
isolated permanently.

65
00:10:20.410 --> 00:10:21.910
Don't worry.
It won't come to that.

66
00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:25.980
I read the report
on the new staff member.

67
00:10:26.010 --> 00:10:27.480
What did you think?

68
00:10:27.520 --> 00:10:31.300
I don't understand why
some grad school superstar...

69
00:10:31.330 --> 00:10:33.750
is being treated
like a seasoned pro.

70
00:10:33.790 --> 00:10:36.380
She's doing ground-breaking
research on pattern nightmares.

71
00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:40.220
We don't need any outside help.
I know these kids.

72
00:10:40.260 --> 00:10:43.160
I don't want some hotshot
taking chances with them...

73
00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:44.830
just so she can get published.

74
00:10:44.870 --> 00:10:47.810
Dr. Gordon. Dr. Simms.
to examination. stat.

75
00:10:50.570 --> 00:10:53.020
This is ridiculous.
I know my daughter.

76
00:10:53.060 --> 00:10:54.790
She's just trying
to get some attention.

77
00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.570
I won't play one of her
little games with her.

78
00:10:56.610 --> 00:10:59.130
Suicide attempt.
Just down from Country General.

79
00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:00.510
- What's her name?
- Kristen Parker.

80
00:11:00.550 --> 00:11:03.060
She was fine
until we tried sedating her.

81
00:11:07.110 --> 00:11:08.700
She tore her stitches out.

82
00:11:08.740 --> 00:11:11.290
Kristen. we want to help you!

83
00:11:12.360 --> 00:11:13.540
Hold her.

84
00:11:18.210 --> 00:11:21.000
I'm Dr. Gordon.
I want to help you.

85
00:11:24.190 --> 00:11:25.920
Be careful. Max!

86
00:11:26.790 --> 00:11:28.190
Back off. Max.

87
00:11:28.230 --> 00:11:31.260
Kristen. put the scalpel down.

88
00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:33.510
Nobody's going to hurt you.

89
00:11:36.680 --> 00:11:40.640
Five. six. grab your crucifix

90
00:11:41.710 --> 00:11:46.370
Seven. eight.
better stay up late

91
00:11:46.720 --> 00:11:51.430
Nine. ten. never. never...

92
00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:52.840
Never sleep again.

93
00:12:00.010 --> 00:12:02.050
Where did you learn that rhyme?

94
00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:16.540
Tell me about the kids.

95
00:12:17.700 --> 00:12:21.350
Well. they're survivors
in a way.

96
00:12:21.390 --> 00:12:23.330
They're all severely
sleep disordered...

97
00:12:23.370 --> 00:12:25.850
insomnia. narcolepsy.
bed-wetting.

98
00:12:25.900 --> 00:12:27.660
But the nightmares
are their common thread?

99
00:12:27.690 --> 00:12:30.410
Right.
They share a group delusion...

100
00:12:30.440 --> 00:12:32.870
a boogieman.
for lack of a better word.

101
00:12:32.900 --> 00:12:34.500
They're so traumatized...

102
00:12:34.530 --> 00:12:36.580
they'll do almost anything
not to sleep.

103
00:12:36.620 --> 00:12:38.000
Anything?

104
00:12:40.520 --> 00:12:43.680
We lost a kid a month ago
to Fairview.

105
00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:45.610
I don't know where
he got the razors...

106
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:47.270
but he cut off his own eyelids
to stay awake.

107
00:12:47.310 --> 00:12:48.970
Oh. God.

108
00:12:49.010 --> 00:12:50.860
Shook the kids up pretty badly.

109
00:12:51.660 --> 00:12:54.820
By the way. that was great work
with the new patient.

110
00:12:54.860 --> 00:12:56.170
Pretty smooth for an intern.

111
00:12:56.200 --> 00:12:59.200
I have had some experience
with pattern nightmares.

112
00:13:00.620 --> 00:13:02.190
I've got to get going.

113
00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:05.610
Let me help you.

114
00:13:08.690 --> 00:13:10.280
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

115
00:13:12.590 --> 00:13:15.370
Now. be sure
that you check in with Max.

116
00:13:15.400 --> 00:13:17.540
He'll give you
the whole twenty-five-cent tour.

117
00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:20.460
I'll see you later.

118
00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:21.900
Oh. Miss Thompson...

119
00:13:21.930 --> 00:13:23.020
You can call me Nancy.

120
00:13:23.950 --> 00:13:25.160
You call me Neil.

121
00:13:25.190 --> 00:13:28.510
What was that nursery rhyme
all about?

122
00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:31.340
It was just something
that the kids say...

123
00:13:31.370 --> 00:13:34.250
to keep the... boogieman away.

124
00:13:57.900 --> 00:13:59.050
Anyway. that's group therapy.

125
00:13:59.440 --> 00:14:02.060
This whole wing
is devoted to the program.

126
00:14:04.170 --> 00:14:05.490
I guess... yeah.

127
00:14:05.520 --> 00:14:07.880
You can use this office
for the time being.

128
00:14:07.920 --> 00:14:09.420
This will be fine.

129
00:14:10.100 --> 00:14:12.040
I'll have you set up
in your own space...

130
00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:13.840
by the end of the week.

131
00:14:13.870 --> 00:14:16.010
The patients' rooms
are down this way.

132
00:14:21.170 --> 00:14:24.400
This is Phillip.
We call him "The Walker."

133
00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:27.280
- Why is that?
- Because I sleepwalk.

134
00:14:27.310 --> 00:14:29.730
A perfectly normal event
that our illustrious staff...

135
00:14:29.780 --> 00:14:32.360
loves to theorize about
endlessly.

136
00:14:32.400 --> 00:14:33.960
Phillip. this is Nancy.

137
00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:37.160
Hi. Welcome to the snake pit.

138
00:14:38.330 --> 00:14:39.330
Thanks.

139
00:14:40.910 --> 00:14:42.160
Nice work.

140
00:14:42.190 --> 00:14:43.850
They really ought to be carved
out of wood...

141
00:14:43.890 --> 00:14:45.550
but they won't let me have
a knife.

142
00:14:47.220 --> 00:14:48.740
I might. you know...

143
00:14:53.430 --> 00:14:57.080
This lump over here is Kincaid.
Take a good look.

144
00:14:57.780 --> 00:15:00.270
He gets himself thrown in
the quiet room so often...

145
00:15:00.310 --> 00:15:02.720
you probably won't see
a lot of him.

146
00:15:02.770 --> 00:15:07.510
I do it so I don't have to look
at your ugly face all the time.

147
00:15:07.540 --> 00:15:08.880
I love you. too.

148
00:15:08.920 --> 00:15:10.130
Nice meeting you.

149
00:15:14.030 --> 00:15:16.940
They're really good kids.
but don't let them fool you.

150
00:15:16.980 --> 00:15:20.140
They're dangerous...
to themselves and to each other.

151
00:15:27.770 --> 00:15:28.910
Hi. Joey.

152
00:15:31.290 --> 00:15:32.950
Why. thank you.

153
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.980
- Hey. Marcie. How you doing?
- Great.

154
00:15:36.020 --> 00:15:39.080
These going to "C" Ward?
I'll walk you down.

155
00:15:40.020 --> 00:15:41.580
See you later. Joey.

156
00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:52.430
Mrs. Parker. was Kristen
acting any different?

157
00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:56.340
Did you notice anything strange
before she made the attempt?

158
00:15:56.380 --> 00:15:58.410
Kristen specializes
in strangeness.

159
00:15:58.460 --> 00:16:00.790
I've spent thousands
on psychiatrists.

160
00:16:02.490 --> 00:16:04.380
Did she always have nightmares?

161
00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:07.220
No. They've gotten worse since
I took away her credit cards.

162
00:16:08.280 --> 00:16:09.690
I'm serious.

163
00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:11.660
I don't know
what you want from me.

164
00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:12.790
Just some answers.

165
00:16:12.830 --> 00:16:14.730
Other kids are involved.
not just Kristen.

166
00:16:14.770 --> 00:16:16.680
All good kids. smart kids.

167
00:16:16.730 --> 00:16:20.050
I'm sorry to hear that.
You're the experts. not me.

168
00:16:20.090 --> 00:16:21.780
If I had any insight
into any of this...

169
00:16:21.810 --> 00:16:23.760
I would share them with you.
believe me.

170
00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:25.210
I'm sure you would.

171
00:16:25.240 --> 00:16:27.150
Excuse me.
I have to get downtown.

172
00:16:27.190 --> 00:16:29.260
I'll need to get her things.

173
00:16:29.300 --> 00:16:32.650
I had them packed
in a suitcase. Teresa.

174
00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:36.950
I'll get them.
Please. I don't mind.

175
00:16:36.990 --> 00:16:39.570
It's the first door
at the top of the stairs.

176
00:21:30.000 --> 00:21:31.590
You.

177
00:21:31.630 --> 00:21:34.210
Oh. my God. Run!

178
00:21:36.660 --> 00:21:38.960
Get us back out. Kristen!
Do it now!

179
00:21:56.460 --> 00:21:58.020
I used to live in this house.

180
00:21:58.060 --> 00:21:59.950
That's just a house
I dream about.

181
00:21:59.980 --> 00:22:02.050
Have you ever done that
before...

182
00:22:02.090 --> 00:22:05.260
pulled someone into your dream?

183
00:22:05.290 --> 00:22:09.260
When I was a little girl.
like four or five...

184
00:22:09.290 --> 00:22:12.260
if I had a nightmare.
I'd always bring my dad in.

185
00:22:13.360 --> 00:22:14.790
The dreams
would always get better.

186
00:22:16.050 --> 00:22:18.430
He used to tell me about it
the next day.

187
00:22:18.920 --> 00:22:21.000
He used to think
they were his dreams.

188
00:22:21.810 --> 00:22:23.630
When did that stop?

189
00:22:24.590 --> 00:22:26.960
When I was still a kid.

190
00:22:26.990 --> 00:22:29.700
My folks got divorced.
and after a while...

191
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:31.540
I just thought
I imagined the whole thing.

192
00:22:32.560 --> 00:22:34.250
I guess I didn't.

193
00:22:34.290 --> 00:22:36.230
It's an amazing gift.

194
00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:40.460
The man in my dreams.
he's real. isn't he?

195
00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:45.960
He's real.

196
00:22:47.150 --> 00:22:49.040
OK. Group's in session.

197
00:22:49.070 --> 00:22:51.340
Straight talk only in this room.

198
00:22:51.380 --> 00:22:54.160
Today I'd like to start
getting us acquainted...

199
00:22:54.190 --> 00:22:57.290
with our new staff member
Nancy Thompson.

200
00:22:57.330 --> 00:22:58.640
Let's make her welcome.

201
00:23:01.680 --> 00:23:03.370
You've already met
Phillip and Kincaid...

202
00:23:03.410 --> 00:23:04.720
and. of course. Kristen.

203
00:23:04.750 --> 00:23:08.650
How about the rest of you tell
Nancy about yourselves?

204
00:23:10.230 --> 00:23:13.090
Will. how about you first?

205
00:23:13.140 --> 00:23:15.310
Hi. I'm Will Stanton.

206
00:23:15.350 --> 00:23:17.970
I've had a little accident.
as you can see...

207
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:19.660
ended up in this chair.

208
00:23:19.700 --> 00:23:23.530
Accident. my ass.
You said this was straight talk.

209
00:23:23.570 --> 00:23:27.500
So he took a jump. He wasn't
sticking needles in his arms.

210
00:23:27.540 --> 00:23:31.880
Save it. Kincaid. Jennifer?

211
00:23:31.920 --> 00:23:33.740
I'm Jennifer Callfield...

212
00:23:33.780 --> 00:23:35.920
and as soon as
I get out of here...

213
00:23:35.960 --> 00:23:38.580
I'm going to Los Angeles
to be an actress.

214
00:23:38.620 --> 00:23:40.720
I'm going to be on TV.

215
00:23:40.750 --> 00:23:43.540
Yeah. "Lifestyle
of the Rich and Psychotic."

216
00:23:43.570 --> 00:23:44.810
Screw you.

217
00:23:47.510 --> 00:23:50.030
This is Joey. He used to be
a debater in school.

218
00:23:50.070 --> 00:23:52.720
Now he doesn't talk much.

219
00:23:53.750 --> 00:23:55.180
I'm Taryn White.

220
00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:57.110
The only reason I'm in here...

221
00:23:57.140 --> 00:23:59.720
is because
it's better than juvie hall.

222
00:23:59.760 --> 00:24:02.830
Also because I'm going through
some very strange shit.

223
00:24:02.870 --> 00:24:04.590
Your dreams?

224
00:24:04.630 --> 00:24:07.150
Everybody has bad dreams.

225
00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:09.570
Can I interject something
just to save time?

226
00:24:09.620 --> 00:24:11.380
Sure. Phillip. go ahead.

227
00:24:11.420 --> 00:24:13.240
According to our kind hosts...

228
00:24:13.270 --> 00:24:15.570
our dreams
are a group psychosis...

229
00:24:15.610 --> 00:24:18.060
sort of a mellow mass hysteria.

230
00:24:18.100 --> 00:24:19.730
The fact that
we all dreamt about this guy...

231
00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:22.390
before we ever met
doesn't impress anybody.

232
00:24:23.870 --> 00:24:25.290
So we go in circles...

233
00:24:25.330 --> 00:24:28.020
making minimal progress
with maximum effort.

234
00:24:28.060 --> 00:24:29.360
You won't make any progress...

235
00:24:29.400 --> 00:24:32.250
until you recognize your dreams
for what they are.

236
00:24:32.280 --> 00:24:33.940
And what are they?

237
00:24:33.970 --> 00:24:36.110
The by-products of guilt.

238
00:24:36.150 --> 00:24:39.930
Psychological scars
stemming from moral conflicts...

239
00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:41.580
and overt sexuality.

240
00:24:41.620 --> 00:24:44.280
Oh. great.
It's my dick that's killing me.

241
00:24:50.040 --> 00:24:52.970
Tell me what's supposed
to be happening again.

242
00:24:53.010 --> 00:24:55.950
You're being attacked
by the bog demon.

243
00:24:57.200 --> 00:24:58.610
Fourteen.

244
00:24:58.650 --> 00:25:00.140
Doesn't count.
You got to say the words.

245
00:25:00.190 --> 00:25:03.510
- This is stupid.
- Come on.

246
00:25:06.870 --> 00:25:11.030
In the name of Lowrek.
Prince of Elves. demon begone.

247
00:25:11.930 --> 00:25:14.900
Good.
You conquered the demon...

248
00:25:14.940 --> 00:25:16.400
but your horse
is sinking in the bog.

249
00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:18.100
What do you do?

250
00:25:19.350 --> 00:25:23.280
I go to bed. and get a new horse
in the morning.

251
00:25:25.080 --> 00:25:27.800
How do I score that...
enchanted slumber or death?

252
00:25:29.330 --> 00:25:31.950
All right. fellas. Lights out.

253
00:25:31.990 --> 00:25:33.550
Aw. Max.

254
00:25:33.590 --> 00:25:35.480
'Aw. Max." You know the rules.

255
00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:37.460
Come on. Joey. You. too.

256
00:25:37.500 --> 00:25:39.800
Every time
we get a good game going...

257
00:25:39.840 --> 00:25:41.290
it's always. "Lights out."

258
00:25:51.810 --> 00:25:54.700
- Good night. fellas.
- Night. Max.

259
00:25:58.780 --> 00:26:00.250
OK. you get first shift.

260
00:26:01.270 --> 00:26:02.970
Oh. come on.
I had it last night.

261
00:26:04.410 --> 00:26:07.260
Good. Just remember.
keep your eyes open...

262
00:26:07.290 --> 00:26:10.870
and one whimper.
and you wake me up. OK?

263
00:26:24.730 --> 00:26:27.700
- This is nice.
- You never been here before?

264
00:26:27.740 --> 00:26:31.090
No. I think it opened
when I was at school.

265
00:26:31.140 --> 00:26:33.280
Best Thai food in Springwood.

266
00:26:33.310 --> 00:26:36.410
Of course. it's the only
Thai food in Springwood.

267
00:26:36.440 --> 00:26:38.810
Do your parents
still live around here?

268
00:26:40.510 --> 00:26:42.170
My mother passed away.

269
00:26:42.210 --> 00:26:44.630
She died in her sleep.

270
00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:46.130
I'm sorry.

271
00:26:47.010 --> 00:26:49.590
My father and I...

272
00:26:49.630 --> 00:26:52.930
Things just seemed
to fall apart after that.

273
00:26:52.960 --> 00:26:55.330
Sounds like a rough time.

274
00:26:55.360 --> 00:26:56.640
It was.

275
00:26:59.650 --> 00:27:03.510
What if I told you that...

276
00:27:03.560 --> 00:27:06.780
your patients
are in real physical danger...

277
00:27:06.820 --> 00:27:08.570
from their dreams?

278
00:27:08.610 --> 00:27:13.050
The nightmares are nothing but
a symptom of the real problems.

279
00:27:13.090 --> 00:27:17.150
Then let's just eliminate
the symptom for the time being.

280
00:27:17.180 --> 00:27:18.910
With Hypnocil?

281
00:27:20.290 --> 00:27:21.460
That's right.

282
00:27:21.500 --> 00:27:23.290
You want me to prescribe...

283
00:27:23.330 --> 00:27:25.120
an experimental
psychoactive drug...

284
00:27:25.150 --> 00:27:27.010
to a bunch
of suicidal teenagers?

285
00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:29.140
Just until we get things
under control.

286
00:27:29.180 --> 00:27:32.160
Dream deprivation is
nothing to fool with.

287
00:27:32.190 --> 00:27:34.270
You have no business
taking it yourself.

288
00:27:34.300 --> 00:27:35.870
I used to be like them.

289
00:27:35.910 --> 00:27:37.840
I know what
they're going through.

290
00:27:37.890 --> 00:27:39.200
So do I.

291
00:27:39.230 --> 00:27:43.970
You told me they were survivors.
and they are.

292
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:47.100
But how much longer
they survive is up to us.

293
00:27:48.960 --> 00:27:50.780
I'm sorry. Nancy.

294
00:27:50.820 --> 00:27:53.030
The answer's no.

295
00:29:12.200 --> 00:29:13.340
Phillip. wake up.

296
00:29:17.870 --> 00:29:20.040
Have a nice stroll. asshole.

297
00:30:05.300 --> 00:30:07.680
What? What are you doing?

298
00:30:07.720 --> 00:30:09.150
Hey! Come on. man!

299
00:30:09.200 --> 00:30:10.820
What are you. crazy?

300
00:30:13.490 --> 00:30:15.310
Oh. shit! What's he doing?

301
00:30:16.270 --> 00:30:18.380
Get help! Get help!

302
00:30:32.360 --> 00:30:34.020
What's the matter?

303
00:30:38.730 --> 00:30:41.320
Don't do it. Phillip!

304
00:30:49.360 --> 00:30:50.820
God! Stop!

305
00:31:21.910 --> 00:31:24.240
I want us to talk
about last night.

306
00:31:24.270 --> 00:31:27.310
I want us to get our feelings
out in the open.

307
00:31:28.980 --> 00:31:32.170
He wasn't strong enough.
so he got wasted. That's all.

308
00:31:32.210 --> 00:31:34.800
That's all?
Is that what you think?

309
00:31:34.840 --> 00:31:37.390
He couldn't hack it.
so he got nailed. Period.

310
00:31:37.430 --> 00:31:41.620
Yeah. Big. tough badass.
How long will you last?

311
00:31:41.650 --> 00:31:43.340
Longer than any of you.

312
00:31:43.370 --> 00:31:46.220
Go ahead and fight.
That's what he wants.

313
00:31:46.260 --> 00:31:47.180
Who?

314
00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:49.450
Who do you think?
What does he want?

315
00:31:49.490 --> 00:31:53.030
To turn us against each other
so we'll be weak.

316
00:31:53.070 --> 00:31:54.930
- Horseshit.
- No. she's right.

317
00:31:54.960 --> 00:31:57.480
We're all
missing the point here.

318
00:31:57.520 --> 00:31:59.950
Phillip's death
was a sleepwalking accident.

319
00:31:59.980 --> 00:32:01.100
Nothing more.

320
00:32:01.140 --> 00:32:05.710
No. I could see him
up there... his face.

321
00:32:05.750 --> 00:32:09.830
He was wide awake...
all the way down.

322
00:32:09.870 --> 00:32:13.380
Then it was suicide.
Phillip quit. He gave up.

323
00:32:13.430 --> 00:32:14.670
Joey says it wasn't suicide.

324
00:32:14.710 --> 00:32:17.420
Listen to me. Joey.
Phillip killed himself.

325
00:32:17.460 --> 00:32:20.080
That's a cowardly thing.
That's an empty thing.

326
00:32:20.120 --> 00:32:22.250
He let himself down.
He let all of us down.

327
00:32:22.290 --> 00:32:25.160
It was murder!
Can't you understand that?

328
00:32:25.200 --> 00:32:27.470
That bastard murdered him!

329
00:32:27.510 --> 00:32:29.580
I'm not listening to this.

330
00:32:29.620 --> 00:32:32.270
How much longer will you go on
blaming your dreams...

331
00:32:32.310 --> 00:32:33.940
for your own weaknesses?

332
00:32:33.980 --> 00:32:37.680
How much longer will you keep
blowing smoke up our ass?

333
00:32:37.720 --> 00:32:39.660
There will be
no repeat occurrences...

334
00:32:39.700 --> 00:32:41.290
of last night's events.

335
00:32:41.330 --> 00:32:44.910
Your doors will be locked
during sleeping hours.

336
00:32:44.950 --> 00:32:47.880
We'll start a policy
of evening sedation.

337
00:32:47.920 --> 00:32:51.310
Anybody tries drugs on me
will get his ass kicked!

338
00:32:51.350 --> 00:32:54.100
You just bought yourself
a night in the quiet room!

339
00:32:54.140 --> 00:32:56.470
- Sit down!
- Fuck you! You sit down!

340
00:32:56.500 --> 00:32:57.650
Easy. Kincaid.

341
00:32:57.680 --> 00:33:01.650
Nobody's putting me to sleep!
Get away! Let me alone!

342
00:33:01.680 --> 00:33:04.070
Ain't nobody
putting me to sleep!

343
00:33:04.120 --> 00:33:06.740
I don't want to go to sleep!

344
00:33:06.780 --> 00:33:08.440
I ain't going to sleep!

345
00:33:08.470 --> 00:33:09.870
Stay in your seats.

346
00:33:11.030 --> 00:33:13.270
We'll begin sedation tonight.
starting with him.

347
00:33:13.300 --> 00:33:16.150
You can't.
They'll be defenseless.

348
00:33:16.190 --> 00:33:18.090
That's precisely
what they need...

349
00:33:18.130 --> 00:33:21.110
some uninterrupted REM sleep
to release that negative energy.

350
00:33:21.140 --> 00:33:23.830
I'm prescribing Hypnocil.

351
00:33:23.870 --> 00:33:25.040
It's a dream suppressant.

352
00:33:25.080 --> 00:33:28.790
I know what it is.
I just can't believe it.

353
00:33:28.830 --> 00:33:30.060
What has she talked you into?

354
00:33:30.100 --> 00:33:32.340
Nothing. It's my decision.

355
00:33:32.370 --> 00:33:35.240
I want these dreams stopped
till we get some answers.

356
00:33:35.290 --> 00:33:37.680
I can't allow that.

357
00:33:37.720 --> 00:33:39.410
Then I'll go to Carver
if I have to.

358
00:33:39.450 --> 00:33:42.130
He'll either back me up
or accept my resignation.

359
00:33:43.390 --> 00:33:46.170
All right.
But if something goes wrong...

360
00:33:46.200 --> 00:33:48.170
I'll make sure
that you're held responsible.

361
00:33:48.220 --> 00:33:50.800
I mean that.
Fully responsible.

362
00:33:53.110 --> 00:33:54.870
I can't believe
I just said that.

363
00:33:54.900 --> 00:33:57.770
Can we get
the Hypnocil by tomorrow?

364
00:33:57.820 --> 00:33:59.570
We're going to try.

365
00:34:00.250 --> 00:34:04.370
I hope you know
what you're getting us into.

366
00:34:10.680 --> 00:34:16.150
Ain't gonna dream no more.
no more

367
00:34:16.190 --> 00:34:20.940
Ain't gonna dream no more

368
00:34:20.990 --> 00:34:26.260
All night long. I sing this song

369
00:34:26.300 --> 00:34:29.680
Ain't gonna dream no more

370
00:34:37.820 --> 00:34:39.220
Girl. what are you doing?

371
00:34:39.260 --> 00:34:41.590
- Watching TV.
- I can see that.

372
00:34:41.630 --> 00:34:44.800
Why don't you read a book?
You watch too much damn TV.

373
00:34:44.830 --> 00:34:45.910
Research.

374
00:34:45.950 --> 00:34:49.110
Right.
You're going to be a TV star.

375
00:34:49.150 --> 00:34:50.680
Wait and see.

376
00:34:50.710 --> 00:34:53.080
If Simms catches you here
after lights out...

377
00:34:53.120 --> 00:34:54.970
she's gonna chew my ass.

378
00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:56.340
I gotta stay up. Max.

379
00:34:57.630 --> 00:34:59.290
Just tonight. please?

380
00:34:59.330 --> 00:35:01.630
I can't handle the nightmare.

381
00:35:03.010 --> 00:35:05.790
Not after Phillip. Not tonight.

382
00:35:13.380 --> 00:35:14.840
I never saw you.

383
00:35:14.870 --> 00:35:16.790
Thanks. Max.

384
00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:39.200
Hi. sweet stuff. Good news.

385
00:35:39.230 --> 00:35:40.990
Can't be good news.
coming from you.

386
00:35:41.030 --> 00:35:43.810
- Pulled night duty.
- So?

387
00:35:43.840 --> 00:35:47.450
So. got the keys to heaven.
baby.

388
00:35:47.490 --> 00:35:50.010
- What?
- The dispensary.

389
00:35:50.040 --> 00:35:53.280
I am talking
clean pharmaceutical high...

390
00:35:53.310 --> 00:35:55.070
a night at Club Meth.

391
00:35:55.110 --> 00:35:56.960
I don't do that shit.

392
00:35:57.000 --> 00:35:59.510
Yeah?
What are those. beauty marks?

393
00:35:59.550 --> 00:36:03.030
- Those are ancient history.
- Oh. yeah?

394
00:36:03.070 --> 00:36:05.630
If you're ever in the mood
for a history lesson...

395
00:36:05.670 --> 00:36:07.810
I'm your teacher. understand?

396
00:36:07.840 --> 00:36:12.600
Stay out of my face.
or I'll go straight to Max.

397
00:36:12.640 --> 00:36:15.960
Who's going to take the word
of a crazy junkie chick?

398
00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:17.310
Fuck off!

399
00:37:06.220 --> 00:37:09.510
It's silly to ask. but how many
of what did they kill?

400
00:37:09.540 --> 00:37:13.150
Don't say that. I love animals.

401
00:37:13.190 --> 00:37:16.190
I bought it red.
so I didn't know what it was.

402
00:37:16.230 --> 00:37:17.920
Probably an artificial bird.

403
00:37:17.950 --> 00:37:19.650
Ever go to acting school?

404
00:37:19.680 --> 00:37:23.360
Not in the beginning.
I started on a talk show.

405
00:37:23.400 --> 00:37:26.460
So you don't always say
you have to study?

406
00:37:26.500 --> 00:37:29.820
I think you should
study. work...

407
00:37:29.870 --> 00:37:32.760
then maybe you can make it.

408
00:37:32.800 --> 00:37:34.910
- Can I ask you something?
- Certainly.

409
00:37:34.950 --> 00:37:37.340
Who gives a fuck what you think?

410
00:37:50.990 --> 00:37:55.590
One. two.
Freddy's coming for you

411
00:37:55.630 --> 00:38:00.260
Three. four.
better lock the door

412
00:38:19.530 --> 00:38:24.230
This is it. Jennifer...
your big break in TV.

413
00:38:24.270 --> 00:38:27.020
Welcome to prime time. bitch!

414
00:38:51.920 --> 00:38:55.040
Don't be ashamed. young man.

415
00:38:55.080 --> 00:38:57.290
This is a place for sorrow.

416
00:38:58.250 --> 00:39:00.110
What faith do you follow?

417
00:39:02.770 --> 00:39:04.140
Science. I suppose.

418
00:39:05.380 --> 00:39:06.810
Sad choice.

419
00:39:06.860 --> 00:39:10.090
There are times when it doesn't
offer much comfort.

420
00:39:14.350 --> 00:39:17.770
I've seen you before. Sister...

421
00:39:17.800 --> 00:39:19.630
Mary Helena.

422
00:39:21.100 --> 00:39:24.420
You do volunteer work
at the hospital.

423
00:39:24.460 --> 00:39:27.910
From time to time.
when I'm needed.

424
00:39:32.530 --> 00:39:35.140
I should have been able
to save them.

425
00:39:35.180 --> 00:39:37.480
Only one thing
can save the children.

426
00:39:37.510 --> 00:39:42.440
The unquiet spirit
must be laid to rest.

427
00:39:42.480 --> 00:39:47.530
It is an abomination
to God and to man.

428
00:39:53.550 --> 00:39:55.620
Excuse me. sister.

429
00:39:57.880 --> 00:39:59.840
What are you doing up here?

430
00:39:59.890 --> 00:40:01.100
I was talking to...

431
00:40:02.770 --> 00:40:04.360
To who?

432
00:40:05.710 --> 00:40:07.560
Doesn't matter.

433
00:40:07.600 --> 00:40:09.490
Are you ready to go now?

434
00:40:09.520 --> 00:40:10.670
Sure.

435
00:40:21.080 --> 00:40:22.530
Are you finished?

436
00:40:22.580 --> 00:40:26.120
Yeah. I'm sorry.
I guess I'm not hungry.

437
00:40:26.160 --> 00:40:27.340
That's OK.

438
00:40:32.210 --> 00:40:34.600
That's pretty. What is that?

439
00:40:37.910 --> 00:40:40.360
This is my Malaysian dream doll.

440
00:40:40.400 --> 00:40:43.370
It's supposed to bring
good dreams.

441
00:40:44.310 --> 00:40:47.130
I could use some of that
right about now.

442
00:40:54.130 --> 00:40:56.500
You know. I used to think...

443
00:40:56.530 --> 00:40:58.190
I could do something
for the kids...

444
00:40:58.230 --> 00:41:00.170
make some kind of difference...

445
00:41:00.210 --> 00:41:03.000
but they're slipping through
my fingers. every one.

446
00:41:04.410 --> 00:41:06.600
You're doing the best
you can for them. Neil.

447
00:41:08.560 --> 00:41:09.640
Am I?

448
00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:12.710
I'm running out of answers.

449
00:41:12.750 --> 00:41:15.820
A patient sleepwalks
out of a high-security ward.

450
00:41:15.860 --> 00:41:17.320
A girl alone in a room dies.

451
00:41:17.370 --> 00:41:19.780
I can't believe
this is happening.

452
00:41:21.080 --> 00:41:22.740
Nothing makes any sense.

453
00:41:26.200 --> 00:41:28.050
Then maybe you're ready.

454
00:41:29.360 --> 00:41:31.250
For what?

455
00:41:31.280 --> 00:41:32.660
The truth.

456
00:41:33.650 --> 00:41:35.410
Try me.

457
00:41:35.610 --> 00:41:37.500
Only if you're willing
to put aside...

458
00:41:37.530 --> 00:41:39.730
everything you've learned
and trust me.

459
00:41:40.880 --> 00:41:42.470
Can you do that?

460
00:41:44.590 --> 00:41:46.060
I can do that.

461
00:41:50.810 --> 00:41:53.110
Straight talk only in this room.

462
00:41:53.140 --> 00:41:55.760
- Is this group?
- Yeah. unofficially.

463
00:41:55.800 --> 00:41:59.480
Soon there won't be enough
of us left to call it group.

464
00:41:59.510 --> 00:42:03.250
Listen up. you guys.
Nancy has something to say.

465
00:42:04.310 --> 00:42:06.620
I know who's trying to kill you.

466
00:42:06.640 --> 00:42:09.490
Don't humor us.
We're not in the mood.

467
00:42:09.530 --> 00:42:13.490
He wears a dirty brown hat.

468
00:42:13.530 --> 00:42:15.440
He's horribly burned.

469
00:42:16.860 --> 00:42:19.750
He has razors on his right hand.

470
00:42:22.230 --> 00:42:23.410
Who is he?

471
00:42:24.640 --> 00:42:26.970
His name is Freddy Krueger.

472
00:42:28.280 --> 00:42:31.150
He was a child murderer
before he died.

473
00:42:31.200 --> 00:42:34.090
And after he died...

474
00:42:34.140 --> 00:42:35.900
he became something worse.

475
00:42:36.500 --> 00:42:41.110
Six years ago.
he killed my friends.

476
00:42:41.140 --> 00:42:42.840
He almost killed me.

477
00:42:42.870 --> 00:42:44.530
Why is he after us?

478
00:42:44.570 --> 00:42:46.770
Yeah. What did we do?

479
00:42:46.810 --> 00:42:48.820
It's not you.

480
00:42:48.850 --> 00:42:53.360
Your parents. my parents...
they burned him alive.

481
00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:56.270
And now we're paying
for their sins.

482
00:42:57.630 --> 00:43:01.210
You are the last
of the Elm Street children.

483
00:43:02.360 --> 00:43:05.180
Mom and Dad...
I mean. that's crazy.

484
00:43:05.210 --> 00:43:06.700
They never mentioned anything...

485
00:43:06.750 --> 00:43:09.470
Sure. Parents tell
their kids that sort of thing...

486
00:43:09.500 --> 00:43:11.380
'Good night. Say your prayers.

487
00:43:11.420 --> 00:43:14.320
"By the way. we torched
some maniac last night."

488
00:43:14.370 --> 00:43:16.570
So what do we do
about this creep?

489
00:43:16.980 --> 00:43:19.120
Kristen is the key.

490
00:43:19.160 --> 00:43:23.220
She has a very special talent.
A gift.

491
00:43:23.260 --> 00:43:25.940
I haven't been able to do that
since I was little.

492
00:43:25.980 --> 00:43:29.330
- You did it the other night.
- That was different.

493
00:43:29.380 --> 00:43:34.190
You never lose a gift like that.
You just forget how to use it.

494
00:43:34.240 --> 00:43:35.990
How about it? Will you try?

495
00:43:38.020 --> 00:43:40.860
All of you have
this inner strength...

496
00:43:40.890 --> 00:43:43.680
some special power
that you've had...

497
00:43:43.700 --> 00:43:45.650
in your most wonderful dreams.

498
00:43:45.690 --> 00:43:49.760
Together. we can learn
to use that power if we try.

499
00:43:49.790 --> 00:43:51.000
You sound like Peter Pan.

500
00:43:52.350 --> 00:43:53.980
Remember. open mind?

501
00:43:55.810 --> 00:43:59.520
Taryn.
would you pull the shades down?

502
00:43:59.550 --> 00:44:02.780
We're going to try
a little group hypnosis.

503
00:44:13.090 --> 00:44:19.130
I want you all to follow
this pendulum with your eyes.

504
00:44:19.160 --> 00:44:20.820
Tune out everything else.

505
00:44:21.790 --> 00:44:24.610
Nothing else exists
but the pendulum.

506
00:44:24.640 --> 00:44:26.680
Take us there. Kristen.

507
00:44:27.650 --> 00:44:30.590
Breathe deeply and relax.

508
00:44:31.750 --> 00:44:34.200
Starting with your toes.
relax everything...

509
00:44:34.240 --> 00:44:36.700
till there's no tension
left in your bodies.

510
00:44:38.690 --> 00:44:40.190
Keep following the pendulum.

511
00:44:42.560 --> 00:44:44.570
You find yourselves
getting tired.

512
00:44:46.280 --> 00:44:48.830
Nothing would feel better
right now...

513
00:44:48.870 --> 00:44:53.990
than a nice. long. deep sleep.

514
00:44:55.400 --> 00:44:57.850
I'm going to count backwards
from five.

515
00:44:57.890 --> 00:45:00.310
When I finish...

516
00:45:00.360 --> 00:45:04.350
you will all be asleep.

517
00:45:05.340 --> 00:45:07.040
Five...

518
00:45:07.070 --> 00:45:08.730
four...

519
00:45:08.770 --> 00:45:10.360
three...

520
00:45:10.400 --> 00:45:12.340
two...

521
00:45:12.380 --> 00:45:13.600
one.

522
00:45:26.020 --> 00:45:27.330
Sorry.

523
00:45:27.360 --> 00:45:29.780
That's OK. We'll try again.

524
00:45:29.830 --> 00:45:31.610
Everybody take five.

525
00:45:38.210 --> 00:45:39.550
I was willing
to go through with this...

526
00:45:39.590 --> 00:45:44.680
for the kids' peace of mind.
but you'll have to face reality.

527
00:46:17.310 --> 00:46:21.060
Joey. I just wanted to get you
alone for a second.

528
00:46:21.090 --> 00:46:24.800
I mean. look. I really like you.

529
00:46:25.670 --> 00:46:27.620
Do you like me?

530
00:46:27.650 --> 00:46:29.060
I know this sounds crazy...

531
00:46:29.090 --> 00:46:32.260
but I make up excuses to come
into the ward every day...

532
00:46:32.300 --> 00:46:34.200
just to see you.

533
00:46:34.250 --> 00:46:36.100
You're so cute.

534
00:46:39.500 --> 00:46:41.800
Let's just try one more time.

535
00:46:41.830 --> 00:46:44.830
If it doesn't work.
I promise I'll...

536
00:46:50.660 --> 00:46:52.230
We're here.

537
00:46:53.190 --> 00:46:56.580
- Where here?
- We're in the dream.

538
00:46:56.620 --> 00:46:59.970
No. we're not.
We're still here in the group.

539
00:47:03.250 --> 00:47:06.210
In my dreams. I can walk.

540
00:47:06.250 --> 00:47:08.360
My legs are strong.

541
00:47:08.400 --> 00:47:11.330
In my dreams.
I am the Wizard Master.

542
00:47:19.750 --> 00:47:22.620
Try something. Kristen.
What can you do in your dream?

543
00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:38.370
A perfect score.
The crowd goes wild.

544
00:47:40.580 --> 00:47:41.670
Dig this.

545
00:47:46.950 --> 00:47:48.970
Kincaid. please.

546
00:47:49.960 --> 00:47:51.370
That's very unnerving.

547
00:47:51.400 --> 00:47:53.160
Hey. check out Taryn.

548
00:47:53.200 --> 00:47:55.330
In my dreams. I'm beautiful...

549
00:47:56.940 --> 00:47:59.550
and bad.

550
00:47:59.590 --> 00:48:03.210
I could get into
a lot of trouble for this.

551
00:48:05.070 --> 00:48:08.420
But I know you won't
say anything. will you?

552
00:48:09.620 --> 00:48:11.660
Unzip me.

553
00:48:24.970 --> 00:48:27.340
Do you like my body. Joey?

554
00:49:14.900 --> 00:49:18.550
What's wrong. Joey?
Feeling tongue-tied?

555
00:49:51.540 --> 00:49:53.400
What's happening?

556
00:49:53.430 --> 00:49:55.250
- He's close.
- Who. Freddy?

557
00:49:55.280 --> 00:49:56.390
He's heavy in the halls.

558
00:49:56.440 --> 00:49:58.290
- Where's Joey?
- Freddy's got him.

559
00:50:02.290 --> 00:50:04.500
Quiet. everyone! Listen.

560
00:50:11.670 --> 00:50:12.620
The room's changing.

561
00:50:14.070 --> 00:50:15.860
What the heck's going on here?

562
00:50:15.890 --> 00:50:17.070
What's happening?

563
00:50:20.720 --> 00:50:23.220
Get away from the wall.

564
00:50:27.930 --> 00:50:29.230
Help!

565
00:50:42.610 --> 00:50:44.470
Don't panic! Quiet down!

566
00:50:49.400 --> 00:50:51.890
This isn't real!

567
00:50:52.500 --> 00:50:53.610
Get us out!

568
00:50:54.390 --> 00:50:55.950
Quiet! The door!

569
00:50:57.850 --> 00:51:00.150
What's going on in here?

570
00:51:00.180 --> 00:51:03.030
What's wrong with Joey?

571
00:51:05.970 --> 00:51:07.220
Code blue.

572
00:51:07.260 --> 00:51:08.500
Oh. my God.

573
00:51:15.710 --> 00:51:18.640
He's in a deep coma.
There's nothing we can do.

574
00:51:18.680 --> 00:51:20.850
This is inexcusable.

575
00:51:20.890 --> 00:51:22.640
The session was unauthorized.

576
00:51:22.680 --> 00:51:24.690
It was purposely conducted
without my knowledge.

577
00:51:24.730 --> 00:51:27.450
Unusual steps were called for.

578
00:51:27.480 --> 00:51:29.680
Is that what I should
tell his parents?

579
00:51:29.720 --> 00:51:32.470
I understand you prescribed
a highly experimental drug.

580
00:51:32.500 --> 00:51:34.130
He's not in a coma...

581
00:51:34.170 --> 00:51:36.660
Your opinion
is of no interest to me.

582
00:51:36.690 --> 00:51:40.630
Furthermore. you've created
panic among the patients.

583
00:51:40.670 --> 00:51:42.490
That's not true.

584
00:51:42.530 --> 00:51:45.830
In four days.
we've had two suicides.

585
00:51:45.880 --> 00:51:47.310
Now he's in a coma.

586
00:51:47.350 --> 00:51:50.650
It's safe to say your approach
has failed. entirely.

587
00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:53.880
You're both relieved of duty.
I want you out today.

588
00:51:57.060 --> 00:51:58.770
I'm sorry. Neil.

589
00:51:58.810 --> 00:52:01.360
I'm afraid
you brought it on yourself.

590
00:52:01.400 --> 00:52:02.810
For God's sake. Elizabeth...

591
00:52:02.840 --> 00:52:05.690
will you please just try
to help the kids?

592
00:52:05.730 --> 00:52:07.660
Will you listen to them?

593
00:52:07.710 --> 00:52:09.430
Of course I will.

594
00:52:14.330 --> 00:52:16.700
What are we going to do?

595
00:52:16.740 --> 00:52:19.100
There's nothing that we can do.

596
00:52:19.130 --> 00:52:21.040
It's out of our hands.

597
00:52:59.040 --> 00:53:00.390
Sister!

598
00:54:38.050 --> 00:54:40.830
This is where it began.

599
00:54:40.870 --> 00:54:43.970
This wing's been closed
for years.

600
00:54:44.010 --> 00:54:46.150
What was this place?

601
00:54:46.180 --> 00:54:50.460
Purgatory... fashioned
by the hands of men.

602
00:54:51.430 --> 00:54:54.750
Twisted. lonely souls.

603
00:54:54.790 --> 00:54:57.720
The worst
of the criminally insane...

604
00:54:58.820 --> 00:55:02.430
were locked up in here
like animals.

605
00:55:02.470 --> 00:55:06.020
This whole facility
was shut down in the forties.

606
00:55:06.060 --> 00:55:07.880
Some sort of scandal?

607
00:55:09.160 --> 00:55:11.520
A young girl on the staff...

608
00:55:11.560 --> 00:55:15.960
was accidentally locked in here
over the holidays.

609
00:55:16.010 --> 00:55:20.160
The inmates
kept her hidden for days.

610
00:55:20.200 --> 00:55:24.390
She was raped...
hundreds of times.

611
00:55:25.550 --> 00:55:29.340
When they found her.
she was barely alive...

612
00:55:29.380 --> 00:55:32.230
and with child.

613
00:55:32.270 --> 00:55:35.330
That girl was Amanda Krueger.

614
00:55:35.370 --> 00:55:36.890
Her child...

615
00:55:38.120 --> 00:55:43.490
The bastard son
of a hundred maniacs.

616
00:55:43.530 --> 00:55:46.850
Some say he was murdered...

617
00:55:46.890 --> 00:55:48.900
though no body was ever found.

618
00:55:51.090 --> 00:55:56.800
You said something before
about laying him to rest.

619
00:55:56.840 --> 00:56:00.160
You must find the remains...

620
00:56:00.210 --> 00:56:03.550
and bury him in hallowed ground.

621
00:56:10.120 --> 00:56:12.220
Hallowed ground?

622
00:56:12.260 --> 00:56:13.730
Sister?

623
00:56:16.140 --> 00:56:20.420
If your only faith is science.
Doctor...

624
00:56:20.460 --> 00:56:24.770
it may be you
that's laid to rest.

625
00:56:27.020 --> 00:56:29.060
Wait!

626
00:56:29.110 --> 00:56:30.630
Sister!

627
00:56:48.980 --> 00:56:51.010
Let go of him. you bastard.

628
00:56:55.660 --> 00:56:56.780
Oh. my God.

629
00:57:08.400 --> 00:57:10.630
I've got to go in.
We have no choice.

630
00:57:10.670 --> 00:57:13.540
Getting yourself killed
won't help the kids at all.

631
00:57:15.340 --> 00:57:17.280
Besides. we do have a choice.

632
00:57:18.410 --> 00:57:20.460
Assuming your mysterious nun
is right.

633
00:57:21.420 --> 00:57:22.670
I've heard weirder things
this week.

634
00:57:25.140 --> 00:57:27.340
All right. Whoever she is...

635
00:57:27.380 --> 00:57:30.190
she seems to know
more about Krueger than I do.

636
00:57:30.230 --> 00:57:33.190
The question is.
what happened to his body?

637
00:57:34.380 --> 00:57:37.320
They burned him to death
in his boiler room...

638
00:57:37.360 --> 00:57:39.050
and they hid the remains.

639
00:57:39.090 --> 00:57:40.500
Who would know
where they're hidden?

640
00:57:41.940 --> 00:57:43.440
Only one man knows...

641
00:57:44.940 --> 00:57:47.600
and it's time for him to talk.

642
00:57:51.640 --> 00:57:54.120
You can't take Nancy
away from us!

643
00:57:54.160 --> 00:57:55.470
She's all we have!

644
00:57:55.510 --> 00:57:57.390
You're a sick girl. Kristen.

645
00:57:57.430 --> 00:57:59.530
If you want to get better.
you must trust me now.

646
00:58:06.890 --> 00:58:09.070
Take her to the quiet room
and sedate her.

647
00:58:10.390 --> 00:58:13.550
You stupid bitch!
You're killing us!

648
00:58:21.140 --> 00:58:23.180
All right. everybody.
Back to bed.

649
00:58:41.200 --> 00:58:42.310
Hi. Daddy.

650
00:58:46.800 --> 00:58:49.300
Well. if it isn't
my little girl.

651
00:58:52.020 --> 00:58:53.970
My baby come to see her daddy?

652
00:58:55.760 --> 00:58:57.420
It's been a long time.

653
00:58:58.740 --> 00:59:00.650
But you're here. Sit down.

654
00:59:01.940 --> 00:59:04.980
What did I do to get so lucky?

655
00:59:05.690 --> 00:59:08.620
I thought that you were
trying to forget me.

656
00:59:09.180 --> 00:59:12.080
That's not true.
You're the one trying to forget.

657
00:59:16.030 --> 00:59:19.340
I need your help. Dad.
Krueger's back.

658
00:59:24.250 --> 00:59:27.510
Fred Krueger is dead.

659
00:59:27.550 --> 00:59:30.710
You always had a little trouble
trying to understand that.

660
00:59:30.740 --> 00:59:32.150
You know what he did.

661
00:59:34.260 --> 00:59:35.670
He's doing it again.

662
00:59:37.370 --> 00:59:38.740
She's telling you the truth.

663
00:59:39.520 --> 00:59:40.660
I don't believe we've met...

664
00:59:40.690 --> 00:59:43.310
and this isn't
any of your goddamn business.

665
00:59:43.350 --> 00:59:48.240
We can stop him this time...
stop him for good...

666
00:59:48.280 --> 00:59:51.220
but we need to know
where his bones were hidden.

667
00:59:53.560 --> 00:59:57.750
I've lost too much
over this already.

668
00:59:57.790 --> 00:59:59.200
I'm through with it.

669
00:59:59.220 --> 01:00:02.290
People are still dying
after all this time.

670
01:00:02.330 --> 01:00:04.370
Stop running away from it.

671
01:00:06.740 --> 01:00:08.720
You owe me.

672
01:00:09.620 --> 01:00:11.440
It was nice seeing you again.
princess.

673
01:00:11.480 --> 01:00:13.870
Next time. don't...

674
01:00:13.920 --> 01:00:15.700
don't stay away so long.

675
01:00:24.510 --> 01:00:27.360
I'll be OK.
Just give me a minute.

676
01:00:30.970 --> 01:00:32.080
It's the hospital.

677
01:00:43.160 --> 01:00:45.050
- Dr. Gordon?
- Taryn.

678
01:00:45.090 --> 01:00:47.930
You've got to come right away.
Kristen had a total shit attack.

679
01:00:47.970 --> 01:00:50.550
Simms doped her up
and put her in the quiet room.

680
01:00:50.580 --> 01:00:53.620
Simms put Kristen
in the quiet room for the night.

681
01:00:53.660 --> 01:00:55.930
- They sedated her.
- Oh. no.

682
01:00:55.970 --> 01:00:58.810
She can't stay awake for long.
She's all alone.

683
01:00:58.840 --> 01:01:01.210
Freddy's going to get her.

684
01:01:01.250 --> 01:01:03.900
Just stay cool.
Help is on the way.

685
01:01:03.940 --> 01:01:05.050
Just hurry!

686
01:01:05.090 --> 01:01:06.500
I got to get there.

687
01:01:06.520 --> 01:01:09.370
- You go. I'll get the remains.
- It's no use.

688
01:01:09.400 --> 01:01:11.920
I'll talk to him.
Make Simms understand.

689
01:01:11.960 --> 01:01:14.010
She'll never understand.
I got to get to Kristen.

690
01:01:15.100 --> 01:01:16.410
Be careful.

691
01:01:30.780 --> 01:01:34.100
My name is Neil Gordon.
Pleased to meet you.

692
01:01:34.150 --> 01:01:35.900
There. now we've met!

693
01:01:35.930 --> 01:01:37.530
Now listen to me!

694
01:01:37.570 --> 01:01:41.460
Maybe you don't care whether
Nancy lives or dies. but I do!

695
01:01:43.420 --> 01:01:46.240
You and I are going
on a little scavenger hunt.

696
01:02:03.520 --> 01:02:04.920
Please. God...

697
01:02:06.370 --> 01:02:08.160
don't make me sleep.

698
01:02:18.920 --> 01:02:20.510
What the hell are we doing here?

699
01:02:25.030 --> 01:02:26.460
I won't be long.

700
01:03:15.660 --> 01:03:16.960
What do you think you're doing?

701
01:03:17.000 --> 01:03:19.940
Look. I'm sorry.

702
01:03:19.970 --> 01:03:23.290
I really need this. I got...

703
01:03:23.330 --> 01:03:25.670
I'll reimburse you.

704
01:03:25.700 --> 01:03:28.450
You keep my driver's license.
I'll be back.

705
01:03:42.280 --> 01:03:44.670
Max. I need to see Kristen.

706
01:03:45.710 --> 01:03:48.640
- You don't understand.
- Save your breath.

707
01:03:48.680 --> 01:03:50.500
Dr. Simms
gave me specific instructions.

708
01:03:50.530 --> 01:03:52.830
No one sees Kristen.
especially you.

709
01:03:52.870 --> 01:03:55.620
But. Max. she needs me.
She's in danger.

710
01:03:55.650 --> 01:03:57.190
You got to believe me!

711
01:03:57.230 --> 01:04:01.090
I really think you mean well.
but my kids been dying off...

712
01:04:01.960 --> 01:04:05.440
and even without Simms' orders.
I wouldn't let you near her.

713
01:04:08.940 --> 01:04:11.320
OK. Max. I understand.

714
01:04:11.370 --> 01:04:13.640
Can I say good-bye
to the others?

715
01:04:13.670 --> 01:04:14.820
I don't know.

716
01:04:14.850 --> 01:04:17.540
It'll be my last chance.

717
01:04:18.800 --> 01:04:21.610
Five minutes.
They're in the TV room.

718
01:04:26.480 --> 01:04:27.880
Where have you been?

719
01:04:27.920 --> 01:04:29.810
There's no time. Come on.

720
01:04:29.830 --> 01:04:32.110
- Where?
- Our last group.

721
01:04:46.450 --> 01:04:47.560
In there.

722
01:04:48.780 --> 01:04:51.850
We knew nobody would ever
find it in that place.

723
01:04:54.190 --> 01:04:56.300
I'm not sure
I can find it myself anymore.

724
01:05:25.960 --> 01:05:28.810
It's deep in the heart
of the place.

725
01:05:28.850 --> 01:05:30.440
Take it slow.

726
01:05:46.610 --> 01:05:48.200
Straight talk only in here.

727
01:05:49.200 --> 01:05:50.610
What about Kristen?

728
01:05:50.640 --> 01:05:52.490
We can't get to her. I tried.

729
01:05:53.490 --> 01:05:56.970
I was hoping we'd have more time
to learn to use the dreams...

730
01:05:57.750 --> 01:06:01.160
but Joey's in there.
Kristen's going in. too.

731
01:06:01.200 --> 01:06:02.790
They need us.

732
01:06:02.830 --> 01:06:05.930
We're trying to go in.
to link up?

733
01:06:05.970 --> 01:06:07.390
It's now or never.

734
01:06:07.440 --> 01:06:10.250
I'm not going to kid you.
This is dangerous.

735
01:06:10.290 --> 01:06:12.710
If you die in this dream.
it's for real.

736
01:06:12.760 --> 01:06:15.310
Nobody has to go in
that doesn't want to.

737
01:06:18.930 --> 01:06:20.490
I'm in.

738
01:06:20.520 --> 01:06:23.460
Me. too.

739
01:06:24.880 --> 01:06:27.700
Let's go kick the motherfucker's
ass all over dreamland.

740
01:06:29.040 --> 01:06:32.590
Remember. you have to stay
together whatever happens.

741
01:06:32.630 --> 01:06:34.520
That's the only way
we can beat him.

742
01:06:40.630 --> 01:06:43.490
All right.
Clear your mind of everything.

743
01:06:48.310 --> 01:06:50.990
Picture yourself
in the quiet room...

744
01:06:51.020 --> 01:06:53.710
the soft. white walls...

745
01:06:53.750 --> 01:06:55.920
the total silence...

746
01:06:55.950 --> 01:06:58.710
only the sound
of your heart beating.

747
01:06:58.730 --> 01:07:01.740
Picture yourself there
with Kristen.

748
01:07:01.780 --> 01:07:05.200
I'm going to count backwards
from five...

749
01:07:05.240 --> 01:07:08.170
and when I'm done.
we'll all be asleep.

750
01:07:08.210 --> 01:07:11.080
We'll all be in the quiet room.

751
01:07:13.360 --> 01:07:14.470
Five...

752
01:07:16.880 --> 01:07:17.940
four...

753
01:07:20.690 --> 01:07:21.800
three...

754
01:07:24.560 --> 01:07:25.680
two...

755
01:07:27.920 --> 01:07:29.030
one.

756
01:07:33.680 --> 01:07:35.090
I knew you'd come.

757
01:07:35.120 --> 01:07:36.950
We wouldn't let you go in alone.

758
01:07:36.980 --> 01:07:39.880
No way. We're a team!

759
01:07:39.930 --> 01:07:43.730
Listen. everybody.
Joey needs us. I can feel him.

760
01:07:43.760 --> 01:07:45.290
Where is he?

761
01:07:46.040 --> 01:07:47.450
How do we find him?

762
01:07:55.760 --> 01:07:57.870
Stay in the middle of the room!

763
01:08:00.640 --> 01:08:01.910
Whatever happens. stay together!

764
01:08:18.650 --> 01:08:21.360
You'll wake up
the whole neighborhood.

765
01:08:22.480 --> 01:08:25.360
Why are you still up?
It's past 1:00.

766
01:08:27.030 --> 01:08:31.090
I just thought I'd wait for you.

767
01:08:31.130 --> 01:08:33.370
Well. I'm home.

768
01:08:33.400 --> 01:08:34.830
You can get to sleep now.
Come on.

769
01:08:34.880 --> 01:08:35.920
Andale.

770
01:08:43.290 --> 01:08:44.700
What's that for?

771
01:08:44.730 --> 01:08:46.640
I'm just glad you're home.

772
01:08:52.670 --> 01:08:55.570
Mom. I had the most awful dream.

773
01:08:55.610 --> 01:08:58.460
Elaine.
where do you keep the bourbon?

774
01:08:58.490 --> 01:08:59.920
I'll be right down.

775
01:09:01.140 --> 01:09:03.030
Kris. I've got a guest.

776
01:09:03.060 --> 01:09:05.450
I just don't want to be alone.

777
01:09:07.610 --> 01:09:11.090
I said
where's the fucking bourbon?

778
01:09:13.280 --> 01:09:15.580
You should listen
to your mother!

779
01:09:15.610 --> 01:09:17.500
God damn it. Kristen.
you ruin everything!

780
01:09:17.540 --> 01:09:19.160
